Hi Garry, 

I was able to get the claim approved today. The GAP payout will be $2501.21. I understand that this leaves a shortfall, and I wanted to explain why this is. 

Please see the below definition for Outstanding Loan Amount:

Outstanding Loan Amount means the amount that is outstanding on your Financing Contract, on the date which the Total Loss occurred, excluding any payment(s) in arrears and any resulting additional interest or penalties, any early settlement charges or fees, any deferred payments, fees or interest charges resulting from any payment holiday agreed between You and Your financing company, any delinquent payments, uncollected service charges, any insurance premiums, termination fees, penalty fees that are owed by You.

As per the transaction history that was submitted, it appears as though there are many payments in arrears. In this scenario, we re-amortize the loan to see what the outstanding loan amount would have been in the event that all payments were made and no additional fees or interest were added to the account.

The actual outstanding loan amount on the date of loss was $29792.74 and the re-amortized outstanding loan amount on the date of loss is $25889.69.

In order for us to send out the cheque to TD Auto Finance we require our proof of loss form to be signed and returned to us. I have attached it to this email. Once I have this back, I can provide you with the tracking number as it becomes available.

Please let me know if you have any questions. 

Thank you, 

Sarah Gabor
